y to the new lingua franca, English? This collection offers answers to these and many other questions through detailed analyses of language and education policies and practices in post-Soviet countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLanguage and educationzFormer Soviet republics. 0aMultilingualismzFormer Soviet republics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBilaniuk, Laada, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBulajeva, Tatjana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiscel, Matthew H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiger, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHogan-Brun, Gabrielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelnyk, Svitlana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMustajoki, Arto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNagzibekova, Mehrinisso, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrusbaev, Abdykadyr, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPavlenko, Aneta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPavlenko, Aneta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aProtassova, Ekaterina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRannut, Mart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSloboda, Marián, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmagulova, Juldyz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102473808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe G